results.title: Shadow City's Most Wanted!
results.description: The FF arrive back in their right time, but in the Negative Zone; they are captured and placed in a virtual reality scenario where they lead criminal lives, constantly thwarted by Lockdown and Rosetta Stone; Reed comes up with a dangerous escape plan.

results.title: Bedlam Breakout
results.description: Lockdown and Rosetta Stone imprison the FF; Reed breaks them out; Sue frees herself from the virtual reality scenario and from Mannequin's shape, then frees the others; they consider taking action against the scenario, and flee before they are recaptured.

results.title: Down & Out in the Negative Zone
results.description: The FF arrive on Annihilus' throneworld; Reed searches for hardware that Annihilus stole from Four Freedoms Plaza, while Ben, Sue, and Johnny battle Annihilus; their combined skills bring them home, to learn that Paris has been overtaken by the Ruined.

results.title: Be it Ever So Humble . . .
results.description: Since Four Freedoms Plaza has been destroyed, the FF move in to their warehouse on Pier Four; Johnny searches for Lyja in vain; as the FF get settled in their new home, they are attacked by Iconoclast, a villain only Sue can see.

results.title: Since the Last Time We Saw Paris -- Itza Been Ruined!
results.description: The FF rescue Margali Szardos from the Ruined; at Pier Four, a teenage girl suddenly appears; Franklin recognizes her as Valeria, remembering her from his special dreams; Bounty arrives to arrest Caledonia; the Bacchae show up to take vengeance on the FF.

results.title: Rascals 4
results.description: Franklin, Valeria, Caledonia, Bounty, Alyssa, and Puppy battle the Bacchae, Hippolyta, Hades, and Cerberus; Valeria runs afoul of Hera; the FF and Hercules come to the rescue, aided by Persephone; Sue meets Valeria, who calls her "Mom."

results.title: Lost Hope!
results.description: Reed investigates Valeria's claim to be Sue's daughter; Sue vents her anger; Valeria overhears; they both reflect on their past; Valeria battles the Absorbing Man and Titania, who drug She-Hulk and Ben; Sue trouces the villains, and brings Valeria home.

results.title: Skull Session
results.description: Valeria makes herself at home in Reed's lab; the FF trace the villains to the San Diego Comic Convention; the Avengers (under influence) attack them; the real villains are the Red Skull and the Mad Thinker, who escape with SHIELD's Helicarrier.

results.title: Last Farewell
results.description: The FF prepare for the arrival of the chaos storm; Valeria vows to protect Franklin; the FF and friends enjoy a fabulous feast; the chaos storm arrives early; Sue sends Franklin, Caledonia, and Puppy to safety; a massive tidal wave looms over Manhattan.

results.title: When Worlds Collide!
results.description: The tidal wave hits Manhattan; Dr. Doom's ship appears; time stops; the FF and Valeria enter the ship and battle Doom's army; they join forces to battle the Dreaming Celestial and rescue Ashema; only Reed and Doom remain standing -- and then only Doom.

results.title: I Am Doctor Doom!
results.description: Valeria hugs Dr. Doom (her "Daddy"); Sue realizes that the man in Doom's armor is her husband; they send Valeria to Haven; "Doom" demands an alliance between his army and the FF; Dorma insists that it be sealed by the wedding of Doom and Sue.

results.title: Say -- What?!
results.description: The world reacts to the news that Sue is going to marry Dr. Doom; Reed tries in vain to free himself from Doom's armor; the Avengers confront Ben about the situation; Namor gives Sue a necklace; Sue marries Doom, and becomes the Baroness von Doom.

results.title: Flashpoint!
results.description: The Pentagon, the Avengers, the villains, and the FF all play out disastrous war scenarios; the Avengers, the FF, and the villains battle; the villains are captured; the Avengers begin to suspect the truth; Reed sends Lancer to find the real Dr. Doom.

results.title: Fear!
results.description: The Frightful Four attack Wyatt Wingfoot's tribe; the FF come to the rescue; Sharon Ventura tries to come to grips with what has been done to her; Sue sees Reed change security protocols and put on Doom's mask by choice; she vows to save her husband.

results.title: Happy New Year, Reed Richards . . . Now Die!
results.description: Reed does research on Iconoclast; Reed battles the Red Ghost's Super-Apes; the Silver Surfer and the Mole Man sense danger; two reporters investigate the monastery where Dr. Doom once sought refuge, to find the monks have all been killed by Crucible.

results.title: Latveria
results.description: The FF travel to Latveria, where Doom and his bride are greeted with acclamation; Sue tries to get used to her new role as Baroness von Doom; Doom contacts Sue, asking her to build a teleport link; Sue struggles with her loyalties, and brings Doom home.

results.title: Doomsday!
results.description: Doom and Reed battle; Doom and Sue disappear; Ben and Johnny find them and learn that Reed is being controlled by Doom's armor; Doom defeats Reed, and reclaims his armor, thus freeing Reed from its control; Doom and the FF bid farewell.

results.title: Abyss
results.description: Sue takes a boat out into the mid-Pacific, where she is attacked; her necklace allows her to breathe underwater and brings Namor to her aid; they are attacked by Dorma; the FF come to the rescue; Sue and Reed affirm their love for each other.

The Enemy Within
results.description: The Silver Surfer and Alicia seek help from the FF; they all go to Yorktown, Saskatchewan, and join forces with the Mole Man in battle against Terminus; Ben gives Alicia and the Surfer his blessing; meanwhile, Crucible threatens the imprisoned reporters.
